  "articleSummary": "**Summary**  \nThe article argues that an AI agent is useless without a standardized way to integrate real‑world services, and introduces the **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** as that solution. It compares MCP to the shift from fragmented USB connectors to universal USB‑C, explaining that once a service implements MCP, any MCP‑compatible agent can call it without writing custom wrappers for each API. The piece provides a tutorial‑style walkthrough using Mastra’s `MCPClient` to connect agents to Google Maps, a weather API, and a local Wikipedia tool, showing how to configure per‑user authentication and compose composite tools. The intended audience is developers building production‑grade AI agents who need scalable, secure, multi‑tenant integrations. The tone is instructional with occasional metaphor (USB‑C) to frame the protocol as a unifying “connector” for AI tools.",
